The paper proposes an approach for natural scene recognition using deep learning techniques, specifically Deep Boltzmann Machines (DBMs). This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper involves unsupervised learning, which falls under the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The use of restricted Boltzmann machines (RBMs) also suggests that the paper may belong to the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves image recognition and classification, which falls under the information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category.
